    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "688cbd49_40a48bad",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/logs/http.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 141,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-10T23:45:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Cloning params seems fine, since:\n* path is just a string, so it\u0027s basically pass by reference\n* storage.Storage is an interface, but I think its usually a pointer\n* LogStreamState is already a pointer.\n\nIt basically makes it the same as if they were passed as real params.  The plus side of cloning it is that since we don\u0027t need to modify anything to send upstream, the caller can be rest assured that data flows in one direction.\n\nWell i guess except for the LogStreamState, since its a pointer :/",
      "parentUuid": "c60e73f6_64eb6e46",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 141,
        "startChar": 56,
        "endLine": 141,
        "endChar": 67
      },
      "revId": "2c65001216bec4ec10a938fe75e39de80d0e2068",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
